  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "r0+9qWeEnqiFVep+jERll3n7MQM=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:28.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "## Problem\n\nPSS messages live only as Trojan chunks and are garbage-collected once the associated postage stamp expires. Chat UX requires history that survives node restarts and stamp rotation.\n\n## Design\n\nEach message is written twice:\n\n1. **Ephemeral PSS send** \u2014 delivers the message to the live peer in 2\u201310s.\n2. **Persistent ACT-encrypted feed append** \u2014 at feed `ph:v2:chatlog:<sorted(alice, bob)>`, entries of the form `{ from, text, timestamp, attachments? }`.\n\nThe feed is uploaded with `{ act: true }` and both users' `beeNodePublicKey` values are registered as ACT grantees via `createGrantees()`. The Bee node handles ECDH decryption transparently when either party reads the feed \u2014 no app-level keys required.\n\n## Implications\n\n- History survives Bee restarts and stamp expiration\n- Either peer's Bee can rebuild the full thread on first open\n- Revocation is possible by rebuilding the ACT with a new access key\n- PSS inbox on reconnect must be reconciled against feed history",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:28.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:28.000Z"
    }
  },
